  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 375f ",
    "butter a 9-inch round cake pan and line the bottom with parchment paper ",
    "whisk together the flour, sugar, and eggs in a medium bowl ",
    "add the vanilla extract, butter, and garlic to the bowl and mix until combined ",
    "pour the mixture into the prepared cake pan and smooth the top ",
    "bake for 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean ",
    "allow the cake to cool in the pan for 5 minutes before transferring it to a wire rack ",
    "whisk together the heavy cream and vanilla extract in a small bowl ",
    "once the cake is cool, drizzle the lacquer glaze over the top of the cake ",
    "serve warm and enjoy"
  ],
